Class WorldGenerator

java.lang.Object
de.oth.blocklib.world.WorldGenerator
public class WorldGenerator
extends java.lang.Object
This class provides any information and method to autogenerate a world.
Author:
Daniel Beer, Stefan Hofweber (WS 2017/2018), Chris Ebbinger (WS 2017/2018)

      public float getInitialSurfaceHeight​(float xPos, float zPos)
      Can be used to determine the initial terrain height at any position. This includes positions where the world is not loaded at the moment.
      Parameters:
      xPos - horizontal x Position
      zPos - horizontal z Position
      Returns:
      the height of the Terrain at any horizontal position.

    • interpolateBiomHeight

      public double interpolateBiomHeight​(double biomNoise, int x, int z)
      Uses the biom noise to calculate the height of the current and the nearest biom terrain. Then calculates and returns a average.
      Parameters:
      biomNoise - value of biom noise
      x - total x coordinate
      z - total z coordinate
      Returns:
      final surface height at X,Z

    • biCubicInterpolation

      biLinearInterpolation - linear factor of average function
      Returns:
      high grade factor of average function
